===Etymology===

{{etyl|ang}} {{term|bryht|lang=ang}}, by metathesis from {{term|beorht|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|berhtaz||berxiaz}}, from {{proto|Germanic|berkhiaz}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|bʰereg-}}. Cognate with Scots ''[[bricht]]'', Upper High German ''[[Bericht]]'', Dutch ''[[bericht]]'', [[brecht]]; Norwegian ''[[bjart]]''; Icelandic ''[[bjartur]]'', French [[brillant]], Spanish [[brillante]], Lithuanian [[breksta]]; Welsh [[berth]]; Sanskrit {{rfscript|Devanagari}} ''bhrajate''. Related to [[bert]], [[Bert]].

